initial commit
Forcing OpenGL to allow version 330 shaders on OS X.
The simple shaders now work as well as all calls to the fixed OpenGL pipeline have been removed.
ShaderProgram replaced with ShaderManager class.
plain_color shader supports changing colors
Entities now respond to setPosition(Vector 3f position) methods and will be placed in the world accordingly.
EntityPlainDrawable can now have its color set using the setColor(R, G, B, A) method.
Entity updates
Missing models added
Velocity on the ball entity
Spacebar now moves the ball.
Input handling.
Input handling.
missing shaders added
Balls now can be dragged and released. Walls are drawn correct.
Added some broken ass collisions.
Increased the FPS limit to 120 to decrease the chance of balls flying through walls.
Roger's course designer format is now interpreted correctly.
played around with the collisions, still sort of broken
now you can putt the ball into the hole
command line parameters now launch the application

Removed old spaghetti code. Re-worked the OBJ loader. Added a SceneManager class. Started work on a TextRenderer. Started work on TextureManager.
OBJ loader in Model should work with EntityProp, but requires models to have UV data.
OBJ models can now be loaded even if they contain no UV map data.
Included the font
